<treatmentCitation id="0A851089FF9AFFA8FF35CE42FE76FEA9" author="" box="[240,424,292,314]" page="27" pageId="1" pageNumber="592">
<bibRefCitation id="EFB54B69FF9AFFA8FF35CE42FE5CFEA9" box="[240,386,292,314]" pageId="1" pageNumber="592" refId="ref805" refString="Remarks. This genus is similar to Krosolus Nielson, 1982 and Srabura Nielson, 1991, but differs from them by the evaginated aedeagus with one group of spines at basal half of shaft, and with or without spines at apical half." type="book chapter">Nielson, 1982</bibRefCitation>
